#: ../../making_first_map.rst:3
msgid "製作第一張地圖"
msgstr "Make Your First Map"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:5
msgid ""
"說到 GMT 中最簡單的繪圖指令，那非 ``pscoast`` 莫屬。在本章中，我們要來解說如何用 ``pscoast`` 製作海岸線地圖、GMT "
"本身的參數輸入風格，以及如何調整這些參數。"
msgstr ""
"The very first command in the beginning is definitely ``pscoast``, which is "
"also the easiest command for mapping. In this chapter, we're going to see "
"how to make a map with coastlines using ``pscoast``. The other topics in "
"this chapter are the style of GMT input and how to set up these input "
"parameters."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:9
msgid "目標"
msgstr "Goal"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:10
msgid ""
"製作一張\\ `群島海 <https://zh.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E7%BE%A4%E5%B2%9B%E6%B5%B7>`_ "
"(Archipelago Sea) 的地圖，如下圖所示。群島海位於北歐，是波羅的海的一個附屬海，海如其\\ "
"名，被大小不等的眾多島嶼給佔據。事實上，群島海很有可能是擁有最多島嶼的海，雖然大部分的島\\ 都很小就是了。西邊的最大島嶼叫做奧蘭島 "
"(Åland)，屬於芬蘭下轄的自治區。這麼多島嶼的地方，\\ 用來觀察 ``pscoast`` 的各種調整效果再適合不過了。"
msgstr ""
"Make a map of `Archipelago Sea <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Archipelago_Sea>`_, as the figure here shows. Located in Northern Europe, "
"Archipelago Sea is actually part of the Baltic Sea. As its name suggests, "
"the sea are actually occupied by numerous islands in any size. Although Most "
"islands are small, Archipelago Sea possibly contains the most island in the "
"world. The largest island in the archipelago is Åland, an autonomous region "
"of Finland. Such a place makes itself ideal to show how ``pscoast`` can fine "
"tune your coasline map."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:20
msgid "直接觀看\\ `指令稿`_"
msgstr "Go to the final `Script`_"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:23
msgid "使用的指令與概念"
msgstr "Commands and Techniques"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:24
msgid "``pscoast`` - **繪製海岸線**"
msgstr "``pscoast`` - **plot shorelines**"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:25
msgid "GMT 共用選項：``-B`` ``-J`` ``-P`` ``-R`` ``-U``"
msgstr "GMT shared options: ``-B`` ``-J`` ``-P`` ``-R`` ``-U``"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:26
msgid "GMT 的命令列參數調整"
msgstr "How to adjust parameters at a GMT command line"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:27
msgid "調整地圖邊框的簡單方法"
msgstr "A simple way to set up map frame"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:28
msgid "GMT 的輸出與轉存"
msgstr "The output file of GMT and how to convert it to other format"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:31
msgid "操作流程"
msgstr "Procedure"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:32
msgid ""
"繪製地圖的第一步，是決定我們繪製的地區。雖然我們已經知道要畫的是群島海了，但沒有詳細的經緯\\ 度是不行的。最方便取得經緯度的作法，就是去 "
"`Google Map <https://www.google.com/maps/>`_ 網站，搜尋 *Archipelago "
"Sea*，然後視窗就會移到這片海域的附近。以右鍵在你想要當作地圖邊界的\\ 區域底點一下，選「\\ *這是哪裡？*\\ "
"」，底下就會出現點選區域的名稱和經緯度。"
msgstr ""
"The first step of plotting a map is to determine where to be plotted. Even "
"though we know we are going to plot Archipelago Sea, we still can't start "
"without a precise map extent. The most convenient way to retrieve map extent "
"in Lat/Long representation is to go to `Google Maps <https://www.google.com/"
"maps/>`_ and search for *Archipelago Sea*. When the map jumps to the region "
"of our interest, right-click on \"*What's here?*\", and the name of the "
"region and its Lat/Long would appear in the bottom."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:39
msgid ""
"注意一下經緯度的表示法，跳出來的視窗中有兩個數字，第一個 `59.865253` 是緯度，正值表示北緯，\\ 負值表示南緯。而第二個 `19."
"435697` 是經度，正值表示東經，負值表示西經。另外，這裡也不採用「\\ "
"度分秒」的角度格式，而是把所有零頭都歸到「度」後的小數點。這種格式比較容易進行數學運算，所以\\ 也是 GMT 預設採用的座標標示法。"
msgstr ""
"Note how longitude and latitude are represented here: there are 2 numbers in "
"the pop-up window. The first one `59.865253` is latitude; positive and "
"negative value are N and S respectively. The second one `19.435697` is "
"longitude; positive and negative value are E and W respectively. Also, it "
"does not use the \"degrees, minutes, secounds\" convention; instead, it "
"converts all minutes and seconds and gives you a real number in degrees. "
"It's much easier to use this format in math calculation, and thus GMT adopts "
"it as the default representation for geographical coordinates."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:44
msgid ""
"查看一番後，這裡我們選擇經度從 19.42 到 22.95，緯度從 59.71 到 60.56 的這塊區域來畫圖。\\ "
"你也可以自由選擇你喜歡的區域。接著打開\\ :ref:`終端機`，輸入如下指令："
msgstr ""
"After taking a look, we are going to select longitude from 19.42 to 22.95 "
"degrees, and latitude from 59.71 to 60.56 degrees for mapping. Also, feel "
"free to try whatever region if you would like! Now, open :ref:`Terminal` and "
"enter the following prompt:"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:47
msgid "$ pscoast"
msgstr "$ pscoast"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:51
msgid ""
"會看到一連串的說明，``pscoast`` 的全部語法和選項都會列在上面。如果你對選項的意思很熟，只是\\ "
"要確認一下的話，你也可以改成這樣輸入，如此一來，就只有選項用法的部份會顯示在螢幕上。"
msgstr ""
"You would see a few pages that show all the syntax and options of "
"``pscoast``. If you've already been super familiar with these options and "
"just want to make sure for the usage, you can also enter command like the "
"following line, ant it will only show the syntax on screen."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:54
msgid "$ pscoast -"
msgstr "$ pscoast -"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:58
msgid "幾乎所有 GMT 的指令，包含 ``pscoast``，都是以類似如下的語法操作："
msgstr ""
"Almost all GMT commands, including ``pscoast`` have a syntax like this:"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:60
msgid "$ 指令 (輸入檔) [選項1 選項2 選項3...]"
msgstr "$ command (input_file) [option1 option2 option3...]"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:64
msgid ""
"所有以負號 (-) 開頭的文字，程式都會解讀成選項，而不是負號開頭的東西，就會是輸入檔。通常每個\\ "
"指令都會有一兩個必填的選項，而其他的選項如果沒指定的話，就會使用預設值。輸入檔和選項的先後次序，\\ 對 GMT "
"而言是沒差的，你也可以打完所有選項後，再打上輸入檔的名字。"
msgstr ""
"Every string starting with a minus sign (-) is interpreted as an **option**, "
"or more technically speaking, a **flag** or an **argument**. If a string "
"doesn't start with a minus sign, it could only be the input file(s). Every "
"GMT command usually has a required option or two; if other options are "
"omitted, defaults settings are used. The order between options and input "
"files don't matter at all. That means, for example, it is ok to enter all "
"options and put the name of input file in the end of line."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:68
msgid ""
"不過 ``pscoast`` 這個指令稍微特別一點點，它\\ **不用給定輸入檔**\\ ！這樣程式要怎麼知道海岸線位在哪呢？\\ 原來，GMT "
"的標準安裝內，已經有附上一個稱為 `GSHHG <https://www.soest.hawaii.edu/pwessel/gshhg/>`_ "
"的資料庫，這個資料庫內含有許多世界的基本資料，像是海岸線、國界、河流等等的位置，而 ``pscoast`` "
"做的事情，就是從這個資料庫裡面讀取資料，畫到地圖上。因此精確說來， ``pscoast`` 不僅能畫海岸線，\\ "
"也可以畫河流、國界等等的特徵。不用給定輸入檔，我們只要專心在設定參數上就行了！第一個參數當然就是\\ 地圖的座標，是透過 ``-R`` (Region) "
"選項來設定的，選項值直接打在 ``-R`` 後方，不需要空格隔開。一般來說， ``-R`` 選項有兩種給定方法："
msgstr ""
"``pscoast`` has got a little special: **an input file is not required!** "
"Given by that, how does the program know where the coastline is? The answer "
"is simple: there is a database called `GSHHG <https://www.soest.hawaii.edu/"
"pwessel/gshhg/>`_ along with the standard installation of GMT. The database "
"contains a lot of basic information of the world, like coastline, country "
"borders, rivers, etc. What ``pscoast`` does is to load data from GSHHS and "
"plot them on your map. Thus, ``pscoast`` is not only capable for drawing "
"coastline but is also used for drawing water bodies and countries. When "
"using ``pscoast``, we only need to focus on setting up options! The first "
"required flag is ``-R`` (Region), which is used to specify extent (covered "
"area) of a map. We can just put all the parameters directly after ``-R``, "
"without any spaces. Normally, there are two ways to specify extent using ``-"
"R`` flag:"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:76
msgid "-R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56\n"
"-R19.42/59.71/22.95/60.56r"
msgstr "-R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56\n"
"-R19.42/59.71/22.95/60.56r"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:81
msgid ""
"第一種格式為 ``西邊界/東邊界/南邊界/北邊界``，也就是由 x 座標 (經度) 和 y 座標 (緯度) 的範圍\\ "
"來指定。第二種格式使用時，要在最後面加上 ``r``，這樣子四個欄位就會是 ``左下角經度/左下角緯度/右上角經度/"
"右上角緯度``。以上兩行實際執行時，效果會一模一樣。這裡我們\\ 來採用第一種格式試試看，在命令行輸入以下指令然後執行看看："
msgstr ""
"The first format is ``W_Border/E_Border/S_Border/N_Border``; that is, we "
"specify the region by x coordinate (longitude) and y coordinate (latitude). "
"The second format needs the coordiates of the bottom-left (BL) corner and "
"the top-right (TR) corner, so it becomes ``BL_long/BL_lat/TR_long/TR_lat``. "
"Don't forget to add an ``r`` if you are using the second way. No matter "
"whichever way you use, it would give you the same result. Here we use the "
"first format and enter the following line in the command prompt:"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:86
msgid ""
"$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56\n"
"pscoast: Syntax error: Must specify a map projection with the -J option\n"
"pscoast: Syntax error: Must specify at least one of -C, -G, -S, -I, -N, -Q "
"and -W"
msgstr ""
"$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56\n"
"pscoast: Syntax error: Must specify a map projection with the -J option\n"
"pscoast: Syntax error: Must specify at least one of -C, -G, -S, -I, -N, -Q "
"and -W"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:92
msgid ""
"馬上就會出現錯誤，問題出在我們還有一些選項沒有給定。對於一張地圖來說，除了邊界以外，第二重要的就是\\ 投影法了。GMT 中以 ``-J`` "
"設定投影法，有五花八門的樣式可供選擇，這裡我們來選個在畫小範圍地圖時很常用的\\ `麥卡托投影法 <https://zh.wikipedia.org/"
"wiki/%E9%BA%A5%E5%8D%A1%E6%89%98%E6%8A%95%E5%BD%B1%E6%B3%95>`_\\ 來看看。輸入以下指令："
msgstr ""
"Oops, an error jumps. The issue here is that we should specify other "
"required arguments as well. Except for map extent, a map projection is also "
"very important for a map. in GMT, ``-J`` flag is used for assigning map "
"projection. There are actually various projections at your service, but here "
"we are going to pick a common one for drawing a regional map: `Mercator "
"projection <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mercator_projection>`_. Enter the "
"following command:"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:97
msgid "$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i"
msgstr "$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:101
msgid ""
"在 ``-J`` 後面的 ``M`` 為麥卡托投影的代號，``6i`` 代表地圖橫向的寬度為 6 英吋 (inch)。\\ "
"如果你對英吋有多長不熟，也可以換成 ``-JM15c``，代表地圖橫向的寬度為 15 公分 (cm)，差不多\\ 就是 6 吋的長度。"
msgstr ""
"The ``M`` after the ``-J`` is the code of Mercator projection, and ``6i`` "
"means that the width of the map is 6 inches. If you don't know how long 6 "
"inches are, just change it into ``-JM15c``. This means the width of the map "
"is 15 centimeters, which is roughly 6 inches wide."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:107
msgid ""
"``-J`` 和 ``-R`` 具有連動關係，也就是說在不同投影法之下，給定地圖邊界和尺寸的方法與參數\\ 輸入模式會有點不同，請參閱\\ **GMT "
"官方說明**\\ 或\\ **之後的章節**。有關於各種投影法的適用情形，\\ 請參閱\\ "
"**之後的章節**\\，或地理資訊系統與測地學專書的介紹。另外，GMT 預設的大地座標系統是 `WGS84 <https://en.wikipedia."
"org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System>`_ 參考橢球，如欲調整此設定，\\ 也請參閱\\ **之後的章節**。"
msgstr ""
"``-J`` and ``-R`` are actually related to each other. When the map "
"projection changes, the way to set map extent and size also changes a little "
"bit. Please see **GMT official documentation** or **later chapter**. For the "
"usage of different map projections, please see **later chapter** or look for "
"it in any GIS or geodesy textbooks. In addition, the default geodetic datum "
"of GMT is `WGS84 <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System>`_ "
"reference ellipsoid. If you would like to change it, plase see **later "
"chapter** as well."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:113
msgid ""
"接下來還有一個錯誤要處理，這是有關「繪圖樣式」的設定。GMT 要求我們至少給定一種繪圖樣式，\\ 我們先使用 ``-W`` "
"以指定海岸線的畫筆屬性。畫筆具有三種屬性：粗細、顏色跟樣式，給定的語法是"
msgstr ""
"Now we still have an error left, which is about the \"drawing style\". GMT "
"asks us to specify at least one drawing style. Firstly, we use ``-W`` for "
"the coastline pen attribute. A pen attribute contains 3 values: thickness, "
"color, and style. The syntax is"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:118
msgid "-W粗細,顏色,樣式"
msgstr "-Wlinewidth,linecolor,linestyle"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:122
msgid ""
"如果省略時，就使用預設的樣式作圖。我們試著指定指定畫筆粗細為 0.1 點 (1 點 = 1/72 英吋 = 0.03527 公分) 的黑色線條看看："
msgstr ""
"If any is omitted, the default is used. Here we try to specify a black pen "
"with a thickness at 0.1 points (1 point = 1/72 inches = 0.03527 cm):"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:125
msgid "$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black"
msgstr "$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:129
msgid ""
"``0.1p`` 代表的就是 0.1 點，``black`` 就是黑色，顯而易見的我們沒有指定線條樣式，程式就會以\\ "
"預設的實心線條作圖。值得一提的還有，我們在這裡使用了 GMT 預先定義的顏色名字，這些名字可以在\\ `這裡 <http://gmt.soest."
"hawaii.edu/doc/5.1.0/gmtcolors.html#list-of-colors>`_\\ 查詢。"
msgstr ""
"``0.1p`` just means 0.1 points, and ``black`` tells GMT to use black pen. "
"Obviously we didn't specify line style here, so GMT will use a soild line. "
"Note that here we used the pre-defined color name in GMT, and all of these "
"names are listed `here <http://gmt.soest.hawaii.edu/doc/5.1.0/gmtcolors."
"html#list-of-colors>`_."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:135
msgid ""
"有關畫筆的進階樣式設定，例如設定線條樣式、利用 RGB 值自訂顏色等，會在「\\ :doc:`pen_and_painting`\\ 」詳加描述。"
msgstr ""
"We will learn the advanced setting for pen attribute, like setting line "
"style or using RGB custom color, in the chapter of \":doc:`pen_and_painting`."
"\""

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:137
msgid "目前已經設定了三個選項，``pscoast`` 已經可以正常執行了。輸入以上指令，如果你看到類似如下畫面："
msgstr ""
"Now we have set 3 arguments up and ``pscoast`` should be able to run "
"smoothly. Type the following command, and if you see this:"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:141
msgid ""
"$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black\n"
"%!PS-Adobe-3.0\n"
"%%BoundingBox: 0 0 595 842\n"
"%%HiResBoundingBox: 0 0 595 842\n"
"%%Title: GMT v5.1.1 (r12968) [64-bit] Document from pscoast\n"
"%%Creator: GMT5\n"
"..... #(太長了，中略)\n"
"end\n"
"%%EOF"
msgstr ""
"$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black\n"
"%!PS-Adobe-3.0\n"
"%%BoundingBox: 0 0 595 842\n"
"%%HiResBoundingBox: 0 0 595 842\n"
"%%Title: GMT v5.1.1 (r12968) [64-bit] Document from pscoast\n"
"%%Creator: GMT5\n"
"..... #(it's pretty long!)\n"
"end\n"
"%%EOF"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:153
msgid ""
"那就表示地圖已經成功產生了！但嚴格來說，GMT 產生的不是地圖，而是一長串以\\ `PostScript <https://zh.wikipedia."
"org/wiki/PostScript>`_ 語言描述的程式碼。我們得把這些程式碼\\ "
"另存成文字檔，然後再找個能夠解讀此種語言的軟體開啟才行。另存新檔的動作，可以透過 UNIX 系統\\ 很常見的 I/O 重導向指令，也就是 "
"``>``，來達成："
msgstr ""
"This means the map has generated successfully! Well, strictly speaking, GMT "
"does not generate a map image but many text lines written in `PostScript "
"<https://zh.wikipedia.org/wiki/PostScript>`_ language. We have to save the "
"codes as a text file, and than open it using software that can interpret "
"this language. It's east to save the output as a file using a common "
"redirecting command in UNIX systems. It is"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:158
msgid "$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black > archi_sea.ps"
msgstr "$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black > archi_sea.ps"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:162
msgid ""
"最後面的 ``> archi_sea.ps`` 是把剛才的純文字輸出轉存到 ``archi_sea.ps`` 中，``.ps`` "
"是這種檔案的常見副檔名。現在就可以用任何一種 :ref:`PostScript 看圖軟體`\\ 來打開此檔案了："
msgstr ""
"The last part ``> archi_sea.ps`` redirects the text output into ``archi_sea."
"ps``. ``.ps`` is a common file extension for PostScript files. Now we are "
"ready to open it using any :ref:`PostScript viewer`."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:167
msgid ""
"為方便閱讀，上圖已旋轉到北方朝上的角度，**實際上的出圖應該會是直向的**。不管怎麼說，這張圖看來\\ "
"幾乎完全不像目標區域的實際樣子，那是因為它只使用了最低限度的參數，尤其是海岸線的數據看起來\\ "
"太過粗糙了。現在我們要來加上一些額外的參數，讓畫出的地圖更能描述實際情況。首先先來為陸地和\\ 海洋加上顏色，使用的分別是 ``-G`` "
"(Ground) 和 ``-S`` (Sea) 選項。"
msgstr ""
"This figure has been rotated so the north is up, for increasing clarity. "
"**The actual map output should be positioned like the next figure.** "
"Nevertheless, This figure looks pretty bad since it doesn't look like the "
"what the targeted area should be. This is because we only used the minimum "
"required arguments. For example, the coastline data used here is too crude "
"to represent the actual shape of islands. Now we are going to add a few more "
"flags to make it better match the real world. First, let us add color for "
"land and sea. We will need ``-G`` (Ground) and ``-S`` (Sea) flags "
"respectively."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:172
msgid ""
"$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black -Gdarkseagreen2 -"
"Scornflowerblue > archi_sea.ps"
msgstr ""
"$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black -Gdarkseagreen2 -"
"Scornflowerblue > archi_sea.ps"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:176
msgid ""
"``darkseagreen2`` 和 ``cornflowerblue`` 都跟 ``black`` 一樣，是 GMT 預先設定的顏色名字。\\ "
"可以看得出來現在指令已經有點長了，這是 GMT 的常態，尤其會在你嘗試調整預設值、畫出更漂亮的地圖時\\ "
"發生。在命令列操作時，這不是什麼大問題，終端機都會自動幫你換行，不過之後如果有要寫 GMT 腳本的需求，\\ 為了排版美觀，可以使用 UNIX "
"常見的接續符號 ``\\``，換行繼續輸入指令。以下指令跟上面的指令效果一模一樣："
msgstr ""
"Like ``black``, ``darkseagreen2`` and ``cornflowerblue`` are also pre-"
"defined color name in GMT. Now the command gets a bit longer, which is quite "
"normal when using GMT, especially when you want to change the defaults and "
"make a pretty map. It's not a problem when a long command are entered at the "
"prompt line because the terminal window would automatically cut a long "
"command into a new line. However, if later you are writing a GMT script and "
"want to make you script neat, you can use the UNIX line-break sign ``\\`` to "
"continue the command at a new line. The following example would give the "
"same result as the previous one:"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:181
msgid ""
"$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black -Gdarkseagreen2 \\\n"
"          -Scornflowerblue > archi_sea.ps"
msgstr ""
"$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black -Gdarkseagreen2 \\\n"
"          -Scornflowerblue > archi_sea.ps"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:186
msgid "本文為了方便閱讀起見，也會使用 ``\\`` 分隔過長的段落，但如果你想要在一行之內完成此道指令，則可以省略\\ 這個符號。"
msgstr ""
"In this tutorial, we also use ``\\`` to break a long command for clarity. If "
"you would like to finish your command in one line, just ignore this line-"
"break sign."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:189
msgid ""
"接下來我們要調整海岸線的解析度。由於有些島真的很小，我們可能要用最高等級解析度的海岸線資料，這些小島\\ 才會呈現在地圖上。``pscoast`` "
"控制輸入資料解析度的選項是 ``-D``，接受的設定值有 ``f`` (full，完整)、\\ ``h`` (high，高)、``i`` "
"(intermediate，中)、``l`` (low，低) 和 ``c`` (crude，粗糙)，預設值是 "
"``l``。這裡我們要用最高等級的解析度，也就是 ``-Df``："
msgstr ""
"Next, we are going to adjust the coastline resolution. This is because some "
"islands in this region are so small that they won't show on a map without a "
"finest resolution. ``pscoast`` use ``-D`` flag to control the coastline "
"resolution. The accepted parameters are ``f`` (full), ``h`` (high), ``i`` "
"(intermediate), ``l`` (low), and ``c`` (crude). The default value is ``l``. "
"Here we use the highest level of resolution, that is, ``-Df``:"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:194
msgid ""
"$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black -Gdarkseagreen2 \\\n"
"          -Scornflowerblue -Df > archi_sea.ps"
msgstr ""
"$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black -Gdarkseagreen2 \\\n"
"          -Scornflowerblue -Df > archi_sea.ps"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:199
msgid "畫出來的 .ps 檔就如下所示"
msgstr "The following figure is the output .ps file."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:205
msgid "由此可見，光是調整海岸線解析度，以及陸地與海洋的顏色，整張圖就會與脫胎換骨。"
msgstr ""
"Here we can see that the map is totally changed by only adjusting coastline "
"resolution and colors for land and sea."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:207
msgid ""
"接下來，或許你已經注意到，每次出圖時，ps 檔總是會有一大塊空白的區域。這是因為 GMT 的運作機制並不是\\ "
"「產生地圖的影像檔」，而是「把地圖印在固定大小的版面上」。如果我們不做任何調整，GMT 的預設版面大小\\ 是橫向 A4 紙張，因此，配上我們約 15 "
"公分的地圖，會有很大一塊留白是必然的。這裡我們暫時不對版面大小\\ 做任何調整，但由於很多的 ps "
"檔看圖軟體的預設版面都是直向紙張，所以輸出的地圖就會像上面一樣，不是以\\ 最「通俗」(北方朝上) 的方向呈現。為了讓我們操作時更方便一點，我們可以加上 "
"``-P`` 選項，命令 GMT 把地圖畫在直向 (Portrait) A4 紙張上。"
msgstr ""
"Maybe you've noticed that there is a always large white space in the output "
"ps file. This is because GMT is not \\\"generating an image of map\\\" but "
"\\\"printing a map on a fixed paper format\\\". If we stick to the default "
"settings, GMT would use landscape-oriented A4 paper. Therefore, our 15-cm-"
"wide map does not totally occupy the paper and leaves a large portion of "
"empty white space. Here we are not going to adjust the paper size, but will "
"address the paper orientation because many PostScript viewers use portrait "
"A4 as default (Microsoft Word does this, too). If we open a landscape-"
"oriented A4 map using the default setting, the map would be rotated and thus "
"the north is not at the top anymore, which is not a conventional map setting."
" To be more convenient, we can add ``-P`` flag, which tells GMT the map "
"should be drawn on a protrait-oriented A4 paper."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:214
msgid ""
"$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black -Gdarkseagreen2 \\\n"
"          -Scornflowerblue -Df -P > archi_sea.ps"
msgstr ""
"$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black -Gdarkseagreen2 \\\n"
"          -Scornflowerblue -Df -P > archi_sea.ps"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:221
msgid ""
"要更改紙張大小的話，得先了解 ``gmtdefaults`` 的相關設定。同樣的，從 ``gmtdefaults`` 中，\\ "
"也可以調整預設紙張的方向，這樣就不用每次都加 ``-P`` 了。與版面設定相關的教學，請看\\ **之後的章節**。"
msgstr ""
"To change paper size, you need to learn the settings in ``gmtdefaults``. "
"Likewise, you can also change the settings in ``gmtdefaults`` directly and "
"then there will be no need to add ``-P``. Please see **later chapter** for "
"setting up paper format in detail."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:224
msgid ""
"目前主圖大致上都完成，剩下邊框需要加入。GMT 使用 ``-B`` 選項設定地圖的邊框與附屬要件，如格線、\\ 座標標誌、底色、標題等等，合起來稱為底圖 "
"(Basemap) 設定。``-B`` 選項是 GMT 中最複雜的選項之一， 有著五花八門的樣式組合可供選擇。這邊我們先講最簡單的兩種組合"
msgstr ""
"Now the main map is almost finished, and it's time to add a map frame. GMT "
"uses ``-B`` to tweak map frame and associated elements, like grids, ticks, "
"annotations and title. They are collectively called the Basemap settings. ``-"
"B`` is one of the most complex arguments in GMT since it's got tons of "
"styles for your choice. Here we are going to introduce 2 simplest "
"combinations:"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:228
msgid "-Ba座標數值間隔f座標刻度間隔g格線間隔\n"
"-B地圖四邊設定+t標題"
msgstr ""
"-Ba(annotation_spacing)f(tick_spacing)g(grid_spacing)\n"
"-B(four_borders)+t(title)"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:233
msgid ""
"第一種組合可以給定地圖邊框的數值、刻度與格線設定，而且使用與 ``-R`` 相同的座標單位，例如 ``-Ba1f1g1`` 代表數值、刻度與格線都是每隔 "
"1 度畫一條，而 ``-Ba2f1`` 是「每隔 2 度標示座標、每隔 1 度\\ 標示刻度，然後不加格線」。第二種組合可以調整地圖的四邊配置，使用 "
"W、S、E、N 來表示東、南、西、北，\\ 大寫表示加上邊框也加上數值，小寫表示只加上邊框而不加數值，如果不加就是不畫邊框。例如 ``-Bwsne`` "
"就是單純畫上邊框，不加上數值顯示 (前面的 a 設定會無效)，而 ``-BWSe`` 則代表「在西方與南方\\ "
"畫邊框且標上數值、在東方單純畫邊框、在北方什麼都不做 (地圖上端會破一個洞)」。第二種組合可以透過 ``+t`` "
"來延伸，後方可以輸入此幅地圖的標題。兩種組合可以同時加在一個指令內，例如說我們的地圖如果這樣設計："
msgstr ""
"The first combination gives the spacing number to annotation (tick mark), "
"tick, and grid. It used the same unit as specified in ``-R``. For example, "
"``-Ba1f1g1`` means annotations, ticks, and grids are plotted at every "
"degree; ``-Ba2f1`` means that \"annotation is labeled every other degree, "
"tick is plotted every degree, and don't add any grid.\" The second "
"combination is for four sides of a map, and it uses W, S, E, N for West, "
"South, East, and North. If it's a capital letter, GMT would put everything "
"(frame and annotations) at this side; if it's a lowercase letter, only frame "
"would be added to this side; if you don't add a letter, nothing will be "
"plotted. For example, ``-Bwsne`` is to put a map frame without any "
"annotation (ignoring the ``-Ba`` setting in the first combination); ``-"
"BWSe`` is to put a frame with annotation at west and south side, but only "
"frame itself at east side (and no frame at the north - the map would look "
"broken!) It's also ok to add ``+t`` at the second combination, which a map "
"title followed by the ``+t`` flag. Two combinations can be both used in the "
"same command. For instance, we can design our map like this:"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:241
msgid ""
"$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black -Gdarkseagreen2 \\\n"
"          -Scornflowerblue -Df -P -Ba2f0.5g1 -BWSne+t\"Archipelago Sea\" \\\n"
"          > archi_sea.ps"
msgstr ""
"$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black -Gdarkseagreen2 \\\n"
"          -Scornflowerblue -Df -P -Ba2f0.5g1 -BWSne+t\"Archipelago Sea\" \\\n"
"          > archi_sea.ps"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:247
msgid ""
"那麼，地圖四邊都會加上邊框，但只有西側和南側會標上經緯度，經緯度會以每 2 度標示一次，\\ 刻度 (黑白線區間) 以每 0.5 度標示一次，格線每 1 "
"度就有一條，而且還會加上 *Archipelago Sea* 這個標題。\\ 畫出來的樣子如下所示："
msgstr ""
"In this case, a map frame us added to all four edges, but annotations are "
"only marked at the west side and the south side. Lat/long annotations are at "
"every 2 degrees, ticks (the black and white bars in the map frame) are 0.5 "
"degrees wide, and grid line is put at every degree. The map is also entitled "
"as *Archipelago Sea*, like the following figure shows:"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:255
msgid ""
"事實上，``-B`` 選項其實是另一個稱為 ``psbasemap`` 指令的精簡版。許多更複雜的邊框設定\\ 可以透過 ``psbasemap`` "
"來達成，如此一來，程式會先畫好邊框，我們再把其他圖層填到邊框內即可。\\ 有關進階的 ``-B`` "
"選項調整，像是自訂數值標記、各軸分開設定、主格線與次要格線、中文字標題與標記等等， 會在\\ **之後的章節**\\ 說明。"
msgstr ""
"Actually ``-B`` is a shortened version of another GMT command called "
"``psbasemap``. We can use ``psbasemap`` to plot many more complex frame "
"settings independently, and then filling the map content into the frame is "
"just simple. For advanced ``-B`` options like custom tick marks, adjusting "
"single axis, primary and secondary grid, and special characters, please see "
"**later chapter**."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:260
msgid ""
"你會發現，群島海的島實在太多，如果我們還想在上面標上其他資訊的話，這些群島很容易讓看地圖的人分心。\\ "
"為了精簡地圖，讓讀者聚焦在關鍵資訊上，``pscoast`` 提供了 ``-A`` 選項，這個選項可以讓我們輸入島嶼\\ 面積 (單位是平方公里)，然後 "
"``pscoast`` 會省略比這個面積還小的島嶼不畫。這裡我們要省略比 0.1 平方\\ 公里還小的島嶼："
msgstr ""
"You would probably feel that ther are too many islands in Archipelago Sea "
"and they easily distract readers, especially if we want to label other "
"information on the map. To simplify our map and make readers focus on key "
"information, ``pscoast`` provides ``-A`` flag to let us specify a minimum "
"area of an island, in square kilometers. Once it's set, ``pscoast`` would "
"ignore any island that is smaller than the given area. Here we are going to "
"make islands that are smaller than 0.1 square kilometers disappear:"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:265
msgid ""
"$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black -Gdarkseagreen2 \\\n"
"          -Scornflowerblue -Df -P -Ba2f0.5g1 -BWSne+t\"Archipelago Sea\" \\\n"
"          -A0.1 > archi_sea.ps"
msgstr ""
"$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black -Gdarkseagreen2 \\\n"
"          -Scornflowerblue -Df -P -Ba2f0.5g1 -BWSne+t\"Archipelago Sea\" \\\n"
"          -A0.1 > archi_sea.ps"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:271
msgid "島嶼比較少，看起來清爽多了，卻又不會喪失「群島海」名稱的霸氣。"
msgstr ""
"With fewer islands, the map looks cleaner but still keeps the sense of its "
"name, \"Archipelago Sea\"."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:275
msgid ""
"我們的地圖目前已大致完成。最後，可以再使用 ``-U`` 選項在右下角加上 GMT 軟體的標誌。``-U`` 選項和 ``-P`` "
"一樣，可以直接加在指令內，不用給定任何值。"
msgstr ""
"Now our map is close to finish. Lastly, let us use ``-U`` flag to add a GMT "
"mark and time stamp at the bottom right corner. The usage of ``-U`` is "
"similar to ``-P`` - it doesn't need any parameters."

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:279
msgid "指令稿"
msgstr "Script"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:281
msgid "本地圖的最終指令稿如下："
msgstr "The final command for our goal is:"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:283
msgid ""
"$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black -Gdarkseagreen2 \\\n"
"          -Scornflowerblue -Df -P -Ba2f0.5g1 -BWSne+t\"Archipelago Sea\" \\\n"
"          -A0.1 -U > archi_sea.ps"
msgstr ""
"$ pscoast -R19.42/22.95/59.71/60.56 -JM6i -W0.1p,black -Gdarkseagreen2 \\\n"
"          -Scornflowerblue -Df -P -Ba2f0.5g1 -BWSne+t\"Archipelago Sea\" \\\n"
"          -A0.1 -U > archi_sea.ps"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:291
msgid ""
"「繪製海岸線圖 - 以 **19.42E - 22.95E，59.71N - 60.56N** 為邊界，麥卡托投影，地圖橫向寬 **6** "
"吋，海岸線的線條使用 **0.1** 點的黑色線，陸地使用 ``darkseagreen2`` 填色，海洋使用 ``cornflowerblue`` "
"填色，使用最高等級解析度\\ 的海岸線資料，直幅繪圖，四邊繪製邊框並在左側和下側標上刻度數值，數值間隔 **2** 度，刻度間隔 **0.5** "
"度，\\ 格線間隔 **1** 度，標題為 *Archipelago Sea*，存檔為 ``archi_sea.ps``。」"
msgstr ""
"\"Plot the coastline map - map extent is set to **(19.42E - 22.95E, 59.71N - "
"60.56N)** in Mercator projection and **6** inches wide. Coastlines are black "
"and **0.1** point wide. Land area is filled with the color "
"``darkseagreen2``, and water area is filled with ``cornflowerblue``. We use "
"the coastline data at full resolution. The map is plotted in portrait mode, "
"with a border frame and annotation marks in the left and bottom. Annotation "
"spacing is **2** degrees, tick spacing is **0.5** degrees, and grid spacing "
"is **1** degree. The map is entitled *Archipelago Sea* and saved as "
"``archi_sea.ps``.\""

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:296
msgid "觀看\\ `最終版地圖`_"
msgstr "Check the `final map`_"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:299
msgid "習題"
msgstr "Exercise"

#: ../../making_first_map.rst:301
msgid ""
"畫出蘇拉威西島 (*Sulawesi*) 的海岸線圖。蘇拉威西島是印尼第四大島，外觀非常有趣，\\ 像是字母 K 或是正在跳舞的人。座標可使用 "
"``118.34E 至 125.70E``，以及 ``6.12S 至 2.08N``。"
msgstr ""
"Make a map illustrating the coastline of *Sulawesi*. Sulawesi is the fourth "
"largest island in Indonesia with an fun shape like the letter K or a dancing "
"person. Use the coordiante ``118.34E to 125.70E`` and ``6.12S to 2.08N``."

